 Mr Mahomed Rafick Vally(62), walked away from his store in Valencia Park, Nelspruit on the morning of 28 May without saying a word. He had left with his silver Mercedes Benz and a missing person’s case was opened at the police station. Mr Vally’s daughter informed www.mobserver.co.za that their frantic search led to the discovery of his passing.
His body was allegedly found in the gorge near Delta Manganese. The cause of death is currently unknown.     Parents frustrated by a lack of space in Middelburg schools Traffic officers to appear in court for corruption #TrafficAlert: Two dead in Kranspoort accidents VIDEO: Two perish after truck jack-knifes • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za